permissions.description: Delete membership status from members in the body that you got this permission from.
Update details of the body that you got the permission from. Might be good for boards, as long as name and legacy key are filtered.
Change the data attached to a body membership in the body you got this permission from
View the members in the body that you got that permission from
Creating bound circles to the body the permission was granted in

Add any member of the body you got this permission from to any bound circle in that body, no matter if the circle is joinable or not or if the member wants that or not. This also allows to add yourself to any circle so only give it to people who anyways have many rights in the body
View members of any circle in the body that you got this permission from
Process join requests in the body that you got the permission from
View join request to the body you got this permission from
Creates a member to the local that this permission was granted in

Update any member in the body you got this permission from. Notice that member information is global and several bodies might have the permission to access the same member. Also don't assign it when not necessary, the member can update his own profile anyways.

View information about all members in the body. This does not allow you to perform a members listing, you might however hold the list:body_memberships permission to perform a members listing of the members in the body

Delete any member from any circle in the body that you got this permission from, even those that you are not in a circle_admin position in or even have member status. Should never be assigned as circle_admins automatically get this permission

Update membership details of members of any circle in the body that you got this permission from, even those that you are not in a circle_admin position in or even have member status. Should never be assigned as circle_admins automatically get this permission
Approve participants and set participant types and statuses for specific boards for Agora statutory events. Would be useful for board members.
Approve participants and set participant types and statuses for specific boards for EPM statutory events. Would be useful for board members.
